{
  "stem": "13251.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was, it was quite an, quite an experience, and-- so anyway, there was basically just two, two other relatives there that maintained communication in the mail with us.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One was my aunt, Gizella, and the other one was Goodmans, which was on my mother's side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also in Cleveland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the ones that were born here, they were kind of distant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't feel it was that significant to find another cousin, [LAUGHS] you know?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's the ones that survived are the ones that try to keep in touch.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was through her efforts, my Aunt Gizella, my father's sister, that she's the one that tried to encourage me to come to the United States, and-- which I really wasn't planning to do, except while I was in the service, I filled out a form for immigration.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I kind of forgot about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it wasn't until years later that my quota came up because I, I had to come on the Czech quota because I was born in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was years before that came up and had I-- if I was married at the time, maybe I wouldn't have come.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I was single.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, what the heck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'll try.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So you had to go by your country of birth, not the Israeli--",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Absolutely, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's automatic.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] There's a-- Israeli citizenship is automatic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One thing that was kind of significant when I came to the United States-- and I always said I'm glad my brother wasn't the one that came here because he would've been totally [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] emotionally upset about what happened is, when I came here, I got a cold shoulder from relatives, yeah, except a couple, you know, the ones that survived.",
      "word_count": 64
    }
  ],
